<article id="post-44657" class="post-44657 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-politics-and-government category-travel-and-places tag-israel tag-perspectives tag-settlements entry kind-">
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://pauljacobson.me/2019/03/27/growing-up-in-an-israeli-settlement/" rel="bookmark">Growing up in an Israeli settlement</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
		<figure class="post-thumbnail">
			<a class="post-thumbnail-inner" href="https://pauljacobson.me/2019/03/27/growing-up-in-an-israeli-settlement/" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1">
				<img width="740" height="430" src="https://i2.wp.com/pauljacobson.me/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Hike_up_Givat_HaTitora-12-2000.jpg?fit=740%2C430&amp;ssl=1" class="attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image jetpack-lazy-image" alt="" data-attachment-id="41768" data-permalink="https://pauljacobson.me/hike_up_givat_hatitora-12-2000/" data-orig-file="https://i2.wp.com/pauljacobson.me/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Hike_up_Givat_HaTitora-12-2000.jpg?fit=2000%2C1324&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="2000,1324" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;2.2&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;NIKON D5100&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1544888550&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;50&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;100&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.0003125&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Hike_up_Givat_HaTitora-12-2000" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://i2.wp.com/pauljacobson.me/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Hike_up_Givat_HaTitora-12-2000.jpg?fit=300%2C199&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i2.wp.com/pauljacobson.me/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Hike_up_Givat_HaTitora-12-2000.jpg?fit=640%2C423&amp;ssl=1" data-lazy-srcset="https://i2.wp.com/pauljacobson.me/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Hike_up_Givat_HaTitora-12-2000.jpg?resize=740%2C430&amp;ssl=1 740w, https://i2.wp.com/pauljacobson.me/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Hike_up_Givat_HaTitora-12-2000.jpg?zoom=2&amp;resize=740%2C430&amp;ssl=1 1480w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 34.9rem) calc(100vw - 2rem), (max-width: 53rem) calc(8 * (100vw / 12)), (min-width: 53rem) calc(6 * (100vw / 12)), 100vw" data-lazy-src="https://i2.wp.com/pauljacobson.me/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Hike_up_Givat_HaTitora-12-2000.jpg?fit=740%2C430&amp;ssl=1&amp;is-pending-load=1" srcset="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7" />			</a>
		</figure>

			
	<div class="entry-content">
		
<div class="wp-block-columns has-2-columns">
<div class="wp-block-column">
<p>I enjoyed Iris Zaki&#8217;s documentary titled &#8220;<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Eac1l1ozfLc">What Itâs Like to Grow Up in an Israeli Settlement</a>&#8220;.  The interviews seem to be part of Zaki&#8217;s documentary film titled &#8220;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.docaviv.co.il/2018-en/films/unsettling/" target="_blank">Unsettling</a>&#8220;.</p>



<p>I especially like how it was an interview with Israelis living in  Tekoa, a settlement town, by an Israeli. If you&#8217;re interested in what  seems to be a pretty honest perspective from Israelis living in one  town, it&#8217;s worth watching this:</p>
</div>



<div class="wp-block-column">
<div data-api-key="pk.eyJ1IjoicGF1bGphY29ic29uIiwiYSI6ImNqbGd5aWk2bTFjbmYzdm51YTM2c3d4NXkifQ.F8Am0PZi07x7wynMbLNaDQ" class="wp-block-jetpack-map" data-map-style="default" data-map-details="true" data-points="[{&quot;placeTitle&quot;:&quot;×ª×§××¢&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;×ª×§××¢&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;×ª×§××¢, Bethlahem, Palestine&quot;,&quot;id&quot;:&quot;place.18669225841619730&quot;,&quot;coordinates&quot;:{&quot;longitude&quot;:35.2293264493346,&quot;latitude&quot;:31.6532800112921}}]" data-zoom="13" data-map-center="{&quot;longitude&quot;:-122.41941550000001,&quot;latitude&quot;:37.7749295}" data-marker-color="red"><ul><li><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&amp;query=31.6532800112921,35.2293264493346">×ª×§××¢</a></li></ul></div>
</div>
</div>



<figure class="wp-block-embed-youtube alignwide wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<span class="embed-youtube" style="text-align:center; display: block;"><iframe class='youtube-player' type='text/html' width='640' height='360' src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/Eac1l1ozfLc?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;fs=1&#038;autohide=2&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;wmode=transparent' allowfullscreen='true' style='border:0;'></iframe></span>
</div><figcaption>&#8220;This week we bring you Iris Zakiâs thought-provoking short film âNatural Born Settlers.â A self-described liberal from cosmopolitan Tel Aviv, Zaki wanted to get behind the politics of Israelâs controversial settlements in the occupied territories â so she moved there, temporarily, setting up an improvised cafe where she could chat with settlers from her own generation.&#8221;</figcaption></figure>



<p>I also enjoyed the Vox documentary series (<a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="1 (opens in a new tab)" href="https://youtu.be/E0uLbeQlwjw" target="_blank">1</a>, <a rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="2 (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B6L9mS9ti6o" target="_blank">2</a>, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_Tlnk0RL5VM" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="3 (opens in a new tab)">3</a>) about Israeli settlements. Most of the documentaries I&#8217;ve watched tend to present pretty dramatic, skewed perspectives of the settlements, and the Vox documentaries seem to be more balanced, given my experiences in Israel so far.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed-youtube alignwide wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
